\chapter{System Development}

\section{Existing System}

The existing system for mental health support mainly depends on traditional methods such as in-person counseling, therapy sessions, and occasional guidance from professionals. While these methods are effective, they have several limitations that make them less accessible and less convenient for many users.

Most mental health services require individuals to visit hospitals or counseling centers physically. This creates difficulty for people who live in remote areas, have busy schedules, or are not comfortable traveling frequently. In addition, booking appointments and waiting for sessions can take a significant amount of time.

Another major issue is the high cost of therapy sessions. Many people cannot afford regular counseling due to financial constraints. This makes mental health support inaccessible to a large section of society.

The availability of trained professionals is also limited. In many regions, especially rural areas, there are not enough mental health experts, which leads to long waiting times and delays in receiving help.

The existing system also lacks continuous daily guidance. Users only receive support during scheduled sessions, and there is no system to help them manage stress or emotions on a daily basis. This results in inconsistency in mental health care.

Additionally, due to social stigma, many people hesitate to seek help. They feel uncomfortable discussing their mental health issues openly and fear being judged by others. This prevents them from taking proper care of their mental well-being.

%---------------- DISADVANTAGES ----------------%
%---------------- DISADVANTAGES ----------------%
\subsection{Disadvantages of Existing System}

\begin{itemize}

\item \textbf{Requires physical presence for counseling sessions:}  
Traditional mental health systems often require individuals to visit clinics or hospitals in person to receive counseling. This can be inconvenient for people with busy schedules, mobility issues, or those living far from healthcare facilities.

\item \textbf{Expensive and not affordable for everyone:}  
Mental health services, including therapy sessions and consultations, can be costly. Many individuals, especially those from low-income backgrounds, may find it difficult to afford continuous treatment or professional help.

\item \textbf{Limited availability of mental health professionals:}  
There is a shortage of qualified mental health professionals in many regions. This leads to long waiting times for appointments and reduces the chances of timely intervention and support.

\item \textbf{Time-consuming due to appointments and travel:}  
Booking appointments, waiting for scheduled sessions, and traveling to healthcare centers consume significant time. This discourages individuals from seeking help regularly.

\item \textbf{No daily support or continuous guidance:}  
Traditional systems typically provide support only during scheduled sessions. There is little to no continuous monitoring or daily guidance, which is crucial for managing ongoing mental health conditions.

\item \textbf{Lack of awareness about self-care practices:}  
Many individuals are not educated about mental health or self-care techniques such as stress management, mindfulness, or emotional regulation, limiting their ability to cope independently.

\item \textbf{Social stigma prevents people from seeking help:}  
In many societies, mental health issues are still stigmatized. Fear of judgment or discrimination prevents individuals from openly seeking professional help or discussing their problems.

\item \textbf{Not easily accessible in rural or remote areas:}  
Mental health facilities are often concentrated in urban areas. People living in rural or remote locations face significant challenges in accessing proper care due to distance, lack of infrastructure, and limited resources.

\end{itemize}
%---------------- PROPOSED SYSTEM ----------------%
\section{Proposed System}

To overcome the limitations of the existing system, we propose HealMate, a web-based mental health support system designed to provide easy, affordable, and accessible mental wellness solutions.

HealMate focuses on providing daily wellness activities, simple remedies, and mental health support through a user-friendly platform. The system allows users to access mental health resources anytime and anywhere using a smartphone or computer.

The proposed system includes features such as daily tasks, mood tracking, health insights, expert consultation, and self-care tips. These features help users maintain emotional balance and improve their mental well-being in a simple and effective way.

One of the key advantages of HealMate is its ease of use. The interface is designed to be simple so that users of all age groups can easily navigate and use the system without any difficulty.

The system also provides continuous support, unlike traditional methods. Users can engage in daily activities and track their progress regularly, which helps in maintaining consistency in mental health care.

