\section{System Architecture}

The system architecture of the HealMate platform is designed as a layered model consisting of the Presentation Layer (Frontend), Backend Services, and Data Layer. This architecture integrates general users and experts into a unified web-based system that supports mental health monitoring, expert interaction, and real-time communication. The structure ensures smooth data flow, scalability, and efficient system performance across web environments.

At the top level, the system includes two primary entities: General Users and Experts. General users include students and individuals seeking mental health support, while experts include professionals and doctors who provide guidance and consultation. Both entities interact with the system through the web-based frontend interface.

\subsection{Presentation Layer (Frontend)}

The presentation layer is implemented as a responsive web interface using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It serves as the primary interaction point between users and the HealMate website. The interface is designed to be user-friendly and accessible across different devices such as desktops, tablets, and smartphones.

The frontend provides separate access for users and experts through authentication modules. General users can register and log in using the user authentication system, while experts access the platform through a dedicated expert authentication module.

After successful login, users are directed to the User Home Dashboard, which includes features such as daily tasks, mood tracking, health insights, and access to the expert hub. These features allow users to monitor their mental health and interact with the platform effectively.

Experts are provided with an Expert Dashboard that enables them to manage their profiles, receive appointment requests, and communicate with users through a real-time chat interface. The frontend also includes a Wellness and Education section that offers guided meditation, yoga exercises, and mental health awareness content.

The presentation layer communicates with backend services using web APIs, ensuring that user interactions are processed dynamically and responses are displayed in real time.

\subsection{Backend Services}

The backend of the system is implemented using Supabase services, which provide the necessary infrastructure for handling web-based application logic and server-side operations. It manages authentication, data processing, and communication between different components of the system.

The backend ensures secure user and expert authentication and manages user sessions. It also handles data exchange between the frontend and the database through APIs.

A key feature of the backend is real-time communication, which enables instant messaging between users and experts through web-based chat functionality. It supports both individual user chat and expert communication services. Additional backend features include storage services, edge functions for server-side execution, and database interaction services.

The backend also supports user management, chat management, and appointment scheduling, ensuring smooth operation of all platform functionalities.

\subsection{Data Layer}

The data layer is implemented using PostgreSQL provided by Supabase. It is responsible for storing and managing all website data in a structured format. The database includes tables for user profiles, expert profiles, authentication details, health metrics such as sleep, water intake, and calorie tracking, appointment records, and chat message history.

The database design ensures proper relationships between tables, enabling efficient data retrieval and consistency. Security mechanisms such as controlled access and data protection are implemented to ensure user privacy and data integrity.

\subsection{Architecture Workflow}

The workflow of the HealMate website begins when a user or expert interacts with the web interface. The request is sent to the backend services through APIs. The backend processes the request, performs operations such as authentication or data handling, and communicates with the database to retrieve or update information.

After processing, the backend sends the response back to the frontend, where it is displayed dynamically to the user. Real-time services ensure that chat communication between users and experts occurs instantly without delay. This continuous interaction between the frontend, backend, and database ensures smooth and efficient functioning of the website.

\subsection{Advantages of System Architecture}

The layered architecture of the HealMate website offers several advantages. It ensures clear separation between frontend, backend, and data layers, improving system organization and maintainability. The architecture supports scalability, allowing the website to handle a growing number of users and data efficiently.

It enables real-time communication, enhancing user experience by providing instant interaction with experts. Secure authentication and data handling mechanisms ensure user privacy and protection. Overall, the architecture provides a reliable, flexible, and efficient framework for delivering mental health support services through a web-based platform.

